            Full job description

            Join a dynamic team as a Financial Diligence Analyst, where you'll play a pivotal role in our client’s rapidly expanding company. You'll be at the forefront of their mergers and acquisitions, ensuring the financial integrity and future success of their target acquisitions. This is your chance to make a significant impact in a thriving industry while working with a supportive and ambitious team. This role is 100% onsite in Birmingham, Alabama.

            Benefits & Extras:
            • Comprehensive health, dental, and vision insurance
            • Generous paid time off and holidays
            • 401(k) plan with company matching
            • Opportunities for professional development and growth
            • Onsite wellness programs and employee assistance resources
            Compensation: $70,000 - $80,000 annually DOE + 10% performance-based bonus

            What You’ll Be Doing:
            • Assisting in the preparation of internal financial analysis workbooks to analyze results
            • Collaborating with business development teams and sellers to collect and analyze financial data
            • Preparing pro forma financial results and forecasting for acquisitions
            • Calculating long-term value creation for capital expenditure projects
            • Analyzing operational expenditure for efficiency
            • Communicating financial results and insights to various teams, including executives
            • Performing ad hoc financial analyses as needed
            What You’ll Need to be Considered
            • Bachelor’s degree in accounting, finance, or a related field
            • 2+ years of experience in financial analysis
            • Advanced proficiency in Excel
            • Strong analytical & reporting skills
            • Excellent communication and presentation skills
            • Ability to manage multiple engagements and meet deadlines
            • Ambitious and comfortable in a fast-paced environment
            Apply now!
